1 transition procedure was performed in accordance
2 with state and federal law,
3 (6) the treatment of any physical injury or illness
4 that would, as certified by a physician, place
5 the individual in imminent danger of death or
6 impairment of a major bodily function unless such
7 treatment is performed, or
8 (7) the provision of puberty-blocking drugs or cross-
9 sex hormones to a person currently receiving such
10 drugs or hormones as of the effective date of
11 this act for a period of not more than six (6)
12 months solely for the purpose of assisting the
13 person with gradually decreasing and
14 discontinuing use of the drugs or hormones.
15 4. "Body dysmorphia affirmation procedures" means a general
16 term encompassing gender transition procedures, anorexia affirmation
17 procedures, and BIID affirmation procedures;
18 5. “Health care provider” means a physician, physician
19 assistant, Advanced Practice Registered Nurse, or any other person
20 who is licensed, certified, or otherwise authorized by the laws of
21 this state to administer health care in the ordinary course of the
22 practice of his or her profession.
23 B. An action for damages for injury or death against any health
24 care provider or hospital licensed under the laws of this state,
Req. No. 10516 Page 4

1 whet her based in tort, breach of contract or otherwise, arising out
2 of body dysmorphia affirmation procedures, shall be brought within
3 twenty (20) years of the date the plaintiff knew or should have
